{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770052663,"nonce":"HUwC6MSMakRAF5CxP2eSANcBywE=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87nsCrn","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/130","origin":"github"},"title":"CLI agents get stuck in interactive git editors (rebase, commit --amend)","message":"## Problem\n\nInteractive git operations (rebase, commit --amend, etc.) that launch editors automatically cause agents to get stuck when using CLI tool interfaces.\n\n**Scenario**: Rebasing PR branch onto main with merge conflicts\n\n```bash\n$ git rebase origin/main\n# ... resolve conflicts ...\n$ git add \u003cfiles\u003e\n$ git rebase --continue\n\n# Git launches $EDITOR (nano/vim) for commit message\n# Agent tries to interact via write_bash tool\n# Gets stuck - can't cleanly exit editor\n```\n\n**Impact**:\n- ❌ Cannot complete rebases to resolve merge conflicts\n- ❌ Requires aborting and working around (fixing on stale branch)\n- ❌ Leaves merge conflicts for humans to resolve manually\n- ❌ Breaks automated PR maintenance workflow\n\n## Example From Session\n\n**Session**: dcd4862f-6c8c-4de5-9645-dce56aae1593\n\nWhile fixing PR #115 review comments:\n1. Checked out PR branch `copilot/add-workspace-validation-tool`\n2. Attempted to rebase onto `origin/main` to resolve conflicts\n3. Resolved Makefile and health_check.sh conflicts\n4. Ran `git rebase --continue`\n5. Nano editor opened for commit message\n6. Tried `{enter}` and `^X` via write_bash tool\n7. Editor didn't close cleanly\n8. Had to abort: `git rebase --abort`\n9. Worked around by fixing issues on existing branch\n10. Merge conflicts still remain in PR\n\n## Root Cause\n\nGit's interactive operations expect terminal control that CLI tool interfaces don't provide:\n- `write_bash` can send input but doesn't get full terminal emulation\n- Nano/Vim keybindings like `^X` don't translate cleanly\n- No visual feedback to know if editor received input\n- Agent can't detect editor state (dirty/clean, waiting for input)\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Solution 1: Set GIT_EDITOR=true (Recommended)\n\nForce git to skip interactive editors:\n\n```bash\n# Before any interactive git operation\nGIT_EDITOR=true git rebase origin/main\nGIT_EDITOR=true git commit --amend\nGIT_EDITOR=true git rebase --continue\n```\n\n**Benefits**:\n- ✅ Works immediately\n- ✅ No editor interaction needed\n- ✅ Uses existing commit messages\n\n**Limitations**:\n- ⚠️ Can't edit commit messages during rebase\n- ⚠️ May auto-accept merge commit messages\n\n### Solution 2: Use --no-edit Flags\n\nWhere available, use flags to skip editing:\n\n```bash\ngit rebase --no-edit origin/main\ngit commit --amend --no-edit\ngit merge --no-edit\n```\n\n**Benefits**:\n- ✅ Explicit intent\n- ✅ Works for most operations\n\n**Limitations**:\n- ⚠️ Not all git commands support --no-edit\n\n### Solution 3: Document in Workflows\n\nAdd to `.agent/workflows/dev/` and `.agent/AI_RULES.md`:\n\n**Guideline**: \"Always use `GIT_EDITOR=true` or `--no-edit` for non-interactive git operations\"\n\n**Example**:\n```bash\n# ❌ Don't do this (will get stuck):\ngit rebase origin/main\n\n# ✅ Do this instead:\nGIT_EDITOR=true git rebase origin/main\n```\n\n## Implementation\n\n1. Update `.agent/workflows/dev/start-feature.md`:\n   - Add GIT_EDITOR=true to rebase examples\n\n2. Update `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh`:\n   - Could add helper function for safe git operations\n\n3. Add to `.agent/AI_RULES.md`:\n   - Section: \"Git Operations for CLI Agents\"\n   - Rule: \"Always disable interactive editors\"\n\n4. Create `.agent/scripts/lib/git_helpers.sh`:\n   ```bash\n   # Safe git rebase that won't hang\n   safe_git_rebase() {\n       GIT_EDITOR=true git rebase \"$@\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n## Alternative: Tool Enhancement (Longer-term)\n\nIf the CLI tool interface could be enhanced to:\n- Detect when a subprocess launches an interactive editor\n- Automatically send exit sequences\n- Or provide a way to run commands with full TTY emulation\n\nThis would be a broader fix but requires tool changes.\n\n## Priority\n\n🟡 Medium - Blocks automated merge conflict resolution, but has workaround (manual rebase)\n\n## Session Evidence\n\nSession: dcd4862f-6c8c-4de5-9645-dce56aae1593\n- Task: Fix PR #115 review comments (issue #99)\n- Attempted: Rebase PR branch onto main\n- Result: Got stuck in nano editor, had to abort\n- Workaround: Fixed issues without resolving merge conflicts\n\n---\n**🤖 Reported-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}